==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sardine
<hw>Sar"dine</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sardine</ets> (cf. Sp. <ets>sardina</ets>, <ets>sarda</ets>, It.
<ets>sardina</ets>, <ets>sardella</ets>), L. <ets>sardina</ets>,
<ets>sarda</ets>; cf. Gr. <?/, <?/; so called from the island of
<etsep>Sardinia</etsep>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one
of several small species of herring which are commonly preserved in
olive oil for food, especially the pilchard, or European sardine
(<spn>Clupea pilchardus</spn>). The California sardine (<spn>Clupea
sagax</spn>) is similar. The American sardines of the Atlantic coast are
mostly the young of the common herring and of the menhaden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sardine</ent>⟦br⟧

